  98     def _get_offset(self, klass, value=1, normalize=False):
  99         # create instance from offset class
 100         if klass is FY5253:
 101             klass = klass(
 102                 n=value,
 103                 startingMonth=1,
 104                 weekday=1,
 105                 variation="last",
 106                 normalize=normalize,
 107             )
 108         elif klass is FY5253Quarter:
 109             klass = klass(
 110                 n=value,
 111                 startingMonth=1,
 112                 weekday=1,
 113                 qtr_with_extra_week=1,
 114                 variation="last",
 115                 normalize=normalize,
 116             )
 117         elif klass is LastWeekOfMonth:
 118             klass = klass(n=value, weekday=5, normalize=normalize)
 119         elif klass is WeekOfMonth:
 120             klass = klass(n=value, week=1, weekday=5, normalize=normalize)
 121         elif klass is Week:
 122             klass = klass(n=value, weekday=5, normalize=normalize)
 123         elif klass is DateOffset:
 124             klass = klass(days=value, normalize=normalize)
 125         else:
 126             klass = klass(value, normalize=normalize)
 127         return klass

 129     def test_apply_out_of_range(self, tz_naive_fixture):
 130         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 131         if self._offset is None:
 132             return
 133 
 134         # try to create an out-of-bounds result timestamp; if we can't create
 135         # the offset skip
 136         try:
 137             if self._offset in (BusinessHour, CustomBusinessHour):
 138                 # Using 10000 in BusinessHour fails in tz check because of DST
 139                 # difference
 140                 offset = self._get_offset(self._offset, value=100000)
 141             else:
 142                 offset = self._get_offset(self._offset, value=10000)
 143 
 144             result = Timestamp("20080101") + offset
 145             assert isinstance(result, datetime)
 146             assert result.tzinfo is None
 147 
 148             # Check tz is preserved
 149             t = Timestamp("20080101", tz=tz)
 150             result = t + offset
 151             assert isinstance(result, datetime)
 152             assert t.tzinfo == result.tzinfo
 153 
 154         except OutOfBoundsDatetime:
 155             pass
 156         except (ValueError, KeyError):
 157             # we are creating an invalid offset
 158             # so ignore
 159             pass

 161     def test_offsets_compare_equal(self):
 162         # root cause of GH#456: __ne__ was not implemented
 163         if self._offset is None:
 164             return
 165         offset1 = self._offset()
 166         offset2 = self._offset()
 167         assert not offset1 != offset2
 168         assert offset1 == offset2

 170     def test_rsub(self):
 171         if self._offset is None or not hasattr(self, "offset2"):
 172             # i.e. skip for TestCommon and YQM subclasses that do not have
 173             # offset2 attr
 174             return
 175         assert self.d - self.offset2 == (-self.offset2).apply(self.d)
 176 
 177     def test_radd(self):
 178         if self._offset is None or not hasattr(self, "offset2"):
 179             # i.e. skip for TestCommon and YQM subclasses that do not have
 180             # offset2 attr
 181             return
 182         assert self.d + self.offset2 == self.offset2 + self.d
 183 
 184     def test_sub(self):
 185         if self._offset is None or not hasattr(self, "offset2"):
 186             # i.e. skip for TestCommon and YQM subclasses that do not have
 187             # offset2 attr
 188             return
 189         off = self.offset2
 190         msg = "Cannot subtract datetime from offset"
 191         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 192             off - self.d
 193 
 194         assert 2 * off - off == off
 195         assert self.d - self.offset2 == self.d + self._offset(-2)
 196         assert self.d - self.offset2 == self.d - (2 * off - off)
 197 
 198     def testMult1(self):
 199         if self._offset is None or not hasattr(self, "offset1"):
 200             # i.e. skip for TestCommon and YQM subclasses that do not have
 201             # offset1 attr
 202             return
 203         assert self.d + 10 * self.offset1 == self.d + self._offset(10)
 204         assert self.d + 5 * self.offset1 == self.d + self._offset(5)

 206     def testMult2(self):

 208             return
 209         assert self.d + (-5 * self._offset(-10)) == self.d + self._offset(50)
 210         assert self.d + (-3 * self._offset(-2)) == self.d + self._offset(6)

 267     def test_immutable(self, offset_types):
 268         # GH#21341 check that __setattr__ raises
 269         offset = self._get_offset(offset_types)
 270         with pytest.raises(AttributeError):
 271             offset.normalize = True
 272         with pytest.raises(AttributeError):
 273             offset.n = 91

 275     def test_return_type(self, offset_types):
 276         offset = self._get_offset(offset_types)
 277 
 278         # make sure that we are returning a Timestamp
 279         result = Timestamp("20080101") + offset
 280         assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 281 
 282         # make sure that we are returning NaT
 283         assert NaT + offset is NaT
 284         assert offset + NaT is NaT
 285 
 286         assert NaT - offset is NaT
 287         assert (-offset).apply(NaT) is NaT

 289     def test_offset_n(self, offset_types):

 291         assert offset.n == 1

 293         neg_offset = offset * -1
 294         assert neg_offset.n == -1

 296         mul_offset = offset * 3

 327     def _check_offsetfunc_works(self, offset, funcname, dt, expected, normalize=False):
 328 
 329         if normalize and issubclass(offset, Tick):
 330             # normalize=True disallowed for Tick subclasses GH#21427
 331             return
 332 
 333         offset_s = self._get_offset(offset, normalize=normalize)
 334         func = getattr(offset_s, funcname)
 335 
 336         result = func(dt)
 337         assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 338         assert result == expected
 339 
 340         result = func(Timestamp(dt))
 341         assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 342         assert result == expected
 343 
 344         # see gh-14101
 345         exp_warning = None
 346         ts = Timestamp(dt) + Nano(5)
 347 
 348         if (
 349             type(offset_s).__name__ == "DateOffset"
 350             and (funcname == "apply" or normalize)
 351             and ts.nanosecond > 0
 352         ):
 353             exp_warning = UserWarning
 354 
 355         # test nanosecond is preserved
 356         with tm.assert_produces_warning(exp_warning, check_stacklevel=False):
 357             result = func(ts)
 358         assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 359         if normalize is False:
 360             assert result == expected + Nano(5)
 361         else:
 362             assert result == expected
 363 
 364         if isinstance(dt, np.datetime64):
 365             # test tz when input is datetime or Timestamp
 366             return
 367 
 368         for tz in self.timezones:
 369             expected_localize = expected.tz_localize(tz)
 370             tz_obj = timezones.maybe_get_tz(tz)
 371             dt_tz = conversion.localize_pydatetime(dt, tz_obj)
 372 
 373             result = func(dt_tz)
 374             assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 375             assert result == expected_localize
 376 
 377             result = func(Timestamp(dt, tz=tz))
 378             assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 379             assert result == expected_localize
 380 
 381             # see gh-14101
 382             exp_warning = None
 383             ts = Timestamp(dt, tz=tz) + Nano(5)
 384 
 385             if (
 386                 type(offset_s).__name__ == "DateOffset"
 387                 and (funcname == "apply" or normalize)
 388                 and ts.nanosecond > 0
 389             ):
 390                 exp_warning = UserWarning
 391 
 392             # test nanosecond is preserved
 393             with tm.assert_produces_warning(exp_warning, check_stacklevel=False):
 394                 result = func(ts)
 395             assert isinstance(result, Timestamp)
 396             if normalize is False:
 397                 assert result == expected_localize + Nano(5)
 398             else:
 399                 assert result == expected_localize
 400 
 401     def test_apply(self, offset_types):
 402         sdt = datetime(2011, 1, 1, 9, 0)
 403         ndt = np_datetime64_compat("2011-01-01 09:00Z")
 404 
 405         for dt in [sdt, ndt]:
 406             expected = self.expecteds[offset_types.__name__]
 407             self._check_offsetfunc_works(offset_types, "apply", dt, expected)
 408 
 409             expected = Timestamp(expected.date())
 410             self._check_offsetfunc_works(
 411                 offset_types, "apply", dt, expected, normalize=True
 412             )

 414     def test_rollforward(self, offset_types):
 415         expecteds = self.expecteds.copy()
 416 
 417         # result will not be changed if the target is on the offset
 418         no_changes = [
 419             "Day",
 420             "MonthBegin",
 421             "SemiMonthBegin",
 422             "YearBegin",
 423             "Week",
 424             "Hour",
 425             "Minute",
 426             "Second",
 427             "Milli",
 428             "Micro",
 429             "Nano",
 430             "DateOffset",
 431         ]
 432         for n in no_changes:
 433             expecteds[n] = Timestamp("2011/01/01 09:00")
 434 
 435         expecteds["BusinessHour"] = Timestamp("2011-01-03 09:00:00")
 436         expecteds["CustomBusinessHour"] = Timestamp("2011-01-03 09:00:00")
 437 
 438         # but be changed when normalize=True
 439         norm_expected = expecteds.copy()
 440         for k in norm_expected:
 441             norm_expected[k] = Timestamp(norm_expected[k].date())
 442 
 443         normalized = {
 444             "Day": Timestamp("2011-01-02 00:00:00"),
 445             "DateOffset": Timestamp("2011-01-02 00:00:00"),
 446             "MonthBegin": Timestamp("2011-02-01 00:00:00"),
 447             "SemiMonthBegin": Timestamp("2011-01-15 00:00:00"),
 448             "YearBegin": Timestamp("2012-01-01 00:00:00"),
 449             "Week": Timestamp("2011-01-08 00:00:00"),
 450             "Hour": Timestamp("2011-01-01 00:00:00"),
 451             "Minute": Timestamp("2011-01-01 00:00:00"),
 452             "Second": Timestamp("2011-01-01 00:00:00"),
 453             "Milli": Timestamp("2011-01-01 00:00:00"),
 454             "Micro": Timestamp("2011-01-01 00:00:00"),
 455         }
 456         norm_expected.update(normalized)
 457 
 458         sdt = datetime(2011, 1, 1, 9, 0)
 459         ndt = np_datetime64_compat("2011-01-01 09:00Z")
 460 
 461         for dt in [sdt, ndt]:
 462             expected = expecteds[offset_types.__name__]
 463             self._check_offsetfunc_works(offset_types, "rollforward", dt, expected)
 464             expected = norm_expected[offset_types.__name__]
 465             self._check_offsetfunc_works(

 544     def test_is_on_offset(self, offset_types):
 545         dt = self.expecteds[offset_types.__name__]
 546         offset_s = self._get_offset(offset_types)
 547         assert offset_s.is_on_offset(dt)
 548 
 549         # when normalize=True, is_on_offset checks time is 00:00:00
 550         if issubclass(offset_types, Tick):
 551             # normalize=True disallowed for Tick subclasses GH#21427
 552             return
 553         offset_n = self._get_offset(offset_types, normalize=True)
 554         assert not offset_n.is_on_offset(dt)
 555 
 556         if offset_types in (BusinessHour, CustomBusinessHour):
 557             # In default BusinessHour (9:00-17:00), normalized time
 558             # cannot be in business hour range
 559             return
 560         date = datetime(dt.year, dt.month, dt.day)
 561         assert offset_n.is_on_offset(date)

 654     def test_pickle_roundtrip(self, offset_types):
 655         off = self._get_offset(offset_types)
 656         res = tm.round_trip_pickle(off)
 657         assert off == res
 658         if type(off) is not DateOffset:
 659             for attr in off._attributes:
 660                 if attr == "calendar":
 661                     # np.busdaycalendar __eq__ will return False;
 662                     #  we check holidays and weekmask attrs so are OK
 663                     continue

 665                 assert getattr(off, attr) == getattr(res, attr)

4159 def get_utc_offset_hours(ts):
4160     # take a Timestamp and compute total hours of utc offset
4161     o = ts.utcoffset()
4162     return (o.days * 24 * 3600 + o.seconds) / 3600.0

4198         valid_offsets = (

4200             if n > 1
4201             else self.valid_date_offsets_singular

4207     def _test_offset(self, offset_name, offset_n, tstart, expected_utc_offset):
4208         offset = DateOffset(**{offset_name: offset_n})
4209 
4210         t = tstart + offset
4211         if expected_utc_offset is not None:
4212             assert get_utc_offset_hours(t) == expected_utc_offset
4213 
4214         if offset_name == "weeks":
4215             # dates should match
4216             assert t.date() == timedelta(days=7 * offset.kwds["weeks"]) + tstart.date()
4217             # expect the same day of week, hour of day, minute, second, ...
4218             assert (
4219                 t.dayofweek == tstart.dayofweek
4220                 and t.hour == tstart.hour
4221                 and t.minute == tstart.minute
4222                 and t.second == tstart.second
4223             )
4224         elif offset_name == "days":
4225             # dates should match
4226             assert timedelta(offset.kwds["days"]) + tstart.date() == t.date()
4227             # expect the same hour of day, minute, second, ...
4228             assert (
4229                 t.hour == tstart.hour
4230                 and t.minute == tstart.minute
4231                 and t.second == tstart.second
4232             )
4233         elif offset_name in self.valid_date_offsets_singular:
4234             # expect the singular offset value to match between tstart and t
4235             datepart_offset = getattr(
4236                 t, offset_name if offset_name != "weekday" else "dayofweek"
4237             )
4238             assert datepart_offset == offset.kwds[offset_name]
4239         else:
4240             # the offset should be the same as if it was done in UTC
4241             assert t == (tstart.tz_convert("UTC") + offset).tz_convert("US/Pacific")

4243     def _make_timestamp(self, string, hrs_offset, tz):
4244         if hrs_offset >= 0:
4245             offset_string = f"{hrs_offset:02d}00"
4246         else:
4247             offset_string = f"-{(hrs_offset * -1):02}00"
4248         return Timestamp(string + offset_string).tz_convert(tz)
